               </msIdentifier>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1. Folio 3r-46r. Anaphora of Our Lady Mary (ʻAkwatēta Qwerbān Zaʻegzeʻtena Māryām) by Abba Heryāqos (Cyriacus) of Behensā Also sometimes called Qeddāsē Māryām.
                     2. Folio 49r-58v. Doctrina Arcanorum (Temherta Hebuʻāt)
                     Provenance
                     Former owner: Walda Sellāsē. Parchment. 60 folios, 1 column, 11-14 lines. Wooden boards, with printed cloth cover. Endnotes: a prayer against smallpox and measles, fols. 47r-48r; an incomplete contract note, fol. 60v.
                     Folios 1r-2v are blank except for pen trials.</summary>
               </msContents>
